revision.text:
The 9th '''[[Central American and Caribbean Games]]''' were held in [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]], the capital city of [[Jamaica]] from August 15 to August 28, 1962. This games included 1,559 athletes from fifteen nations. It took place days after the country had gained independence from the United Kingdom. It is the first and so far only Central American and Caribbean Games to be held in a non-Spanish-speaking country.

