The '''2016 [[BBC Music Awards]]''' took place on 12 December in [[London]] at [[ExCeL London]]. Two new awards were introduced, the [[BBC Radio 1]] [[Live Lounge]] Performance of the Year award and the [[BBC Radio 2]] Album of the Year award. The first winner of the former was [[The 1975]], who performed "[[What Makes You Beautiful]]" (originally by [[One Direction]]) and the winner of the latter award was [[Adele]] for her album ''[[25 (Adele album)|25]]''. 

The major winner{{weasel-inline|date=March 2017}} of the night was [[Adele]] who won two awards to the Album of the Year and Song of the Year.

==Hosts==
The awards were hosted by [[Fearne Cotton]], [[Claudia Winkleman]] and [[Gemma Cairney]]. [[Niki Albon|Niki]] & [[Sammy Albon|Sammy]] Albon were backstage hosts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teneightymagazine.com/2016/12/08/niki-and-sammy-to-host-bbc-music-awards/|title=Niki and Sammy to Host at BBC Music Awards – TenEighty — YouTube News, Features, and Interviews|website=teneightymagazine.com}}</ref>

