{{unreferenced|date=August 2008}} {{Infobox military conflict |conflict=Battle of Lize |partof=[[Warring States period]] |image= |caption= |date= 478 BC |place= |casus= |territory= |result=Yue victory |combatant1=[[Wu (state)|Wu]] |combatant2=[[Yue (state)|Yue]] |commander1= Fu Chai |commander2= Gou Jian |strength1= 50,000 |strength2= 50,000 |casualties1=30,000-45,000 |casualties2=1,000-10,000 }} The '''Battle of Lize''' (笠泽之战) was fought between the states of [[Wu (state)|Wu]] and [[Yue (state)|Yue]] in the [[Warring States period]] of [[Chinese history]]. In 478 BC, Yue attacked Wu and defeated Wu's army.
After this battle, Wu lost much of its power while Yue gained much territory, reversing the strength of the two states.
