er His "Epiphany"?|accessdate=September 26, 2018|date=April 10, 2018|author=Townsend, Catherine}}</ref> Later that afternoon, Schiendelman's vehicle was seen by multiple witnesses crossing several lanes of traffic (with no apparent driver) before crashing into the center median; one witness reported seeing an unknown man exit the vehicle from the passenger door and run into the woods. Schiendelman's whereabouts remain unknown. |- |data-sort-value="2016-07-13"|2016 |{{nowrap|[[Disappearance of Kristal Reisinger|Kristal Reisinger]]}} |29 (31 {{as of|2018|lc=y}}) |Kristal Reisinger, a mother of one, disappeared mysteriously on 13 July 2016 from [[Crestone, Colorado]] and has been missing since. |- |data-sort-value="2016-09-24"|2016 |[[Disappearance of Corrie McKeague|Corrie McKeague]] |23 (25 {{as of|2018|lc=y}}) |Corrie McKeague, a member of the [[Royal Air Force Regiment]], went missing from [[Bury St Edmunds]], [[Suffolk|Suffolk, England]] on the morning of 24 September 2016. Despite an extensive search and public appeals no trace of him has been found.<ref>{{cite web|title=Find Corrie McKeague|url=http://www.findcorrie.co.uk/|website=find Corrie McKeague|accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> |- |data-sort-value="2016-10-15"|2016 |[[Disappearance of Najeeb Ahmed|Najeeb Ahmed]] |27 (29 {{as of|2018|lc=y}}) |Najeeb Ahmed, a first year M.Sc. [[Biotechnology]] student from [[Jawaharlal Nehru University, Delhi|Jawaharlal Nehru University]] in [[New Delhi|New Delhi, India]], disappeared under suspicious circumstances on 15 October 2016 from his [[Campus|college campus]] and has not been seen since.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mallick |first1=Abhilash |date=20 March 2017 |title=Kidnapped, Missing, or Still in JNU: Where Is Najeeb Ahmed? |url=https://www.thequint.com/india/2016/10/28/kidnapped-missing-or-still-in-jnu-where-is-najeeb-ahmed-mother-jnusu-abvp |publisher=The Quint |access-date=7 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=28 October 2016 |title=JNU issues 25-point bulletin on Najeeb, no mention of brawl |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/JNU-issues-25pt-bulletin-on-Najeeb-no-mention-of-brawl/articleshow/55079326.cms |publisher=The Times of India |access-date=7 August 2017 }}</ref> |- |data-sort-value="2017-06-09"|2017 |[[Disappearance of Yingying Zhang|Yingying Zhang]] |26 (27 {{as of|2018|lc=y}}) |Yingying Zhang, a Chinese visiting scholar conducting research at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana–Champaign]], was last seen on 9 June 2017 in [[Urbana, Illinois]]. Security cameras captured her getting into a car at the corner of West Clark Street and North Goodwin Avenue around 2:04&nbsp;p.m. that day. Police arrested Brendt Christensen on 30 June 2017 and charged him with kidnapping Zhang and believe, based on available evidence, that she is no longer alive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.justice.gov/usao-cdil/pr/champaign-man-arrested-charged-kidnapping-visiting-scholar|title=Champaign Man Arrested, Charged with Kidnapping Visiting Scholar|publisher=U.S. Department of Justice}}</ref> |- |data-sort-value="2017-08-08"|2017 |[[Zelim Bakaev]] |25 (26 {{as of|2018|lc=y}}) |Russian Chechen singer Zelim Bakaev disappeared in [[Chechnya]] on 8 August 2017 while on a brief visit to the region to attend his sister's wedding. It is widely believed that he had been abducted, tortured, and murdered by the Chechen authorities as part of their [[LGBT rights in Chechnya#Anti-gay persecution in 2017|systematic persecution of homosexuals]].<ref name=sun>{{cite news|last=Charlton|first=Corey|date=25 October 2017|title=SINGER 'PURGED': Gay pop star Zelimkhan Bakaev 'tortured to death' in sickening anti-LGBT purge in Russian hellhole Chechnya|url=https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/4761396/gay-pop-star-zelimkhan-bakaev-tortured-to-death-in-sickening-anti-lgbt-purge-in-russian-hellhole-chechnya/|work=[[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]}}</ref> |- |data-sort-value="2018-01-25"|2018 |[[Tomasz Mackiewicz]] |43 |Polish mountain climber Tomas